HIV/AIDS: China ta ce ta samu karuwar 14 cikin 100 na sababbin kamuwa da cutar
Kasar Sin ta ba da rahoton karuwar kashi 14 cikin 100 na yawan mutanen da ke dauke da cutar HIV da AIDS.
Hukumar lafiya ta ce, mutane fiye da 820,000 ne suka ji rauni a ƙasar.
A cikin kwata na biyu na 2018 kadai, an samu sabbin mutane 40,000.
Mafi yawan sababbin cututtuka sun kasance na jima'i, kuma wannan sabon abu ne.
A wasu sassa na ƙasar Sin, cutar HIV ta yi sauri domin an yi amfani da jini don a yi wa mutane shan jini.
Amma, adadin mutanen da ke kamuwa da cutar HIV ta wannan hanyar ya ragu zuwa kusan sifili, kamar yadda hukumomin kiwon lafiya na kasar Sin suka faɗa a wani taro a lardin Yunnan.
Amma a cikin shekara guda, adadin mutanen da ke da cutar HIV da AIDS a ƙasar Sin ya ƙaru da mutane 100,000.
Cutar HIV da ake watsawa ta hanyar jima'i babbar matsala ce a cikin al'ummar LGBT a kasar Sin.
A shekara ta 1997, an halatta jima'i tsakanin mutane guda biyu, amma ana cewa nuna bambanci ga 'yan luwadi a tsakanin mutane ɗaya da ɗaya ya zama ruwan dare.
Wasu bincike sun nuna cewa kashi 70 zuwa 90 cikin 100 na maza da suke yin jima'i da maza suna yin aure da mata saboda ra'ayoyin da suka dace da ƙasar.
Yawancin cututtuka na cututtuka sun faru ne saboda rashin amfani da maganin hana haihuwa a cikin waɗannan yanayin.
Tun shekara ta 2003, gwamnatin kasar Sin ta yi alkawarin samun damar yin amfani da maganin HIV kyauta da daidaito a ƙoƙarin magance matsalar.
